            <!-- Project One Row -->
            <div class="row justify-content-center no-gutters mb-5 mb-lg-0">
                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <img class="img-fluid" src="~/img/bg_rara.jpeg" alt="">
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <div class="bg-black text-center h-100 project">
                        <div class="d-flex h-100">
                            <div class="project-text w-100 my-auto text-center text-lg-left">
                                <h4 class="text-white">Rara - Heaven at Earth</h4>
                                <p class="mb-0 text-white-50">
                                    You know what am I proud of? People may be proud of their achievements, properties, knowledge and other tangible things. Yeah, life has been easier with these goods but does that really count? Do these things make you happier every time you catch a sight on? If so, then I must say you haven't explored the world behind those things. As a human, the only thing that fascinated me is nature, which I have got to embrace from the early days. The beauty and the freshness and the built-up adrenaline within me whenever I get to have a sight on nature, make me proud; proud to the extent that I cry sometimes..actually most of the time. The culture of humans that we have been brought up has let us down; seriously. The culture to embrace the mother nature has been in shadow ever since the culture to achieve, envy and hurdle for so-called success that we might not get happy when we actually get it. So why wait..explore the world. Money counts but that does not mean you have to sacrifice your motive of life for that paper.
                                    Rara can be your next destination for this wholesome new adventure. I had been there with a couple of friends in 2017. I can still smile looking onto those memories I made there at Rara. The clean and shining water and the reflection of the mountains onto those crystal clear lake water was a sight I would never forget of. The wildness within that domesticated horses and the chirping of the birds under the canopy of those colorful trees was the best thing I ever witnessed. The steep walkthrough marching with my friends was an incredible moment that will remain till my last breath.
                                    Stop confusing yourself with money as a pursuit of life. Make memories. Money can wait while your life couldn't.
                                </p>
                                <hr class="d-none d-lg-block mb-0 ml-0">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
