                                <h4 class="text-white">Friends -  Part of Life</h4>
                                <p class="mb-0 text-white-50">
                                    WhatIf humans were introvert? Single answer: Death. In my view, the only thing worthy of being human is that they are sociable. Unlike some who do not value the existence of the nearby people, we call them as friends. Once a stranger, next will be friends. The intent of socializing with other humans is the only thing human possess. Making friends is not hard as it seems to be. Believe me, social gestures like Namaste and a smile with greetings will do your work.The above picture reminds me of the good old times I got to spend with my friends. A night stay at Sunkoshi Beach Camp was a moment where we all took a moment of our life away from our hectic schedules and made a memorable one. The nightlong conversation about the future plans and the willingness to achieve something more in life were spilled out from each one of us. Although I am the youngest one from the group, I also delivered insights on my future goals and prejudice for the days to come. It was a hopeful and intriguing moment that will forever be engraved in my life. My humble reminder to all of you to take a break, give your self a time so that you could believe and reconstruct on the work that you always wanted to do.
                                </p>
